VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\b(backdoor|bypass|sneaky|exploit|unauthorized_access|unauthorized_entry|hidden_entry|stealthy_entry|secret_entry)\b
WHEN EXPR MISSING:(?i)\b(example|sample|dummy|test|placeholder|ctf|training)\b
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects the presence of keywords commonly associated with backdoor entries or methods used to bypass security restrictions in code.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for Backdoor Entry and Bypass Detection.
